=== Summer Internship Journey at Inara Technologies – Week 1 of 6===

I am excited to share that I have started my 6-week Summer Internship at Inara Technology. During the first week, I focused on building a strong foundation in Linux system administration, DevOps, containerization, and Kubernetes fundamentals.

Some of the key concepts and tools I have learned so far include:

🔹 Linux Basics

* Navigating the Linux file system using commands such as pwd, ls, and cd
* Creating and managing files and directories with mkdir and touch
* Understanding file permissions and ownership using chmod and chown
* User and group management with useradd and groupadd
* Working with sudo for administrative tasks

🔹 Text Processing & Scripting

* Searching and filtering data using grep
* Editing text streams with sed
* Processing structured data using awk
* Executing shell scripts and understanding automation basics

🔹 Package & Service Management

* Managing software packages with apt and dpkg
* Starting, stopping, and monitoring services using systemctl
* Viewing and analyzing system processes with ps, top, and kill

🔹 System Monitoring & Scheduling

* Exploring logs with journalctl
* Creating scheduled tasks using cron jobs and systemd timers

🔹 Storage & Networking

* Understanding disk and filesystem management with lsblk, df, and mount
* Learning secure remote access through SSH, SSH keys, and SCP

🔹 Web Server Administration

* Introduction to Nginx configuration and service management

🔹 RAID Fundamentals

* Basic RAID management concepts using mdadm

🔹 Docker Fundamentals

* Understanding containerization concepts
* Working with Docker images and containers using docker pull, docker run, and docker ps

🔹 Kubernetes Basics

* Learning core Kubernetes concepts such as Pods and Deployments
* Managing Kubernetes resources with kubectl commands
* Deploying and monitoring applications in a Kubernetes environment

This first week has provided me with valuable hands-on exposure to modern infrastructure and DevOps practices. I look forward to learning more advanced topics throughout the remaining weeks of my internship and will continue sharing my progress as I complete additional modules and reports assigned by the company.

